{{Infobox song | title = We'll Knock The Heligo-- Into Heligo-- Out Of Heligoland! | English_title = | comment = | image = | caption = Sheet Music cover | alt = | original_artist = | recorded_by = | performed_by = | written = | Released = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | Published = 1917 | Length = <!-- {{Duration|m=MM|s=SS}} --> | Writer = John J. O'Brian | Composer = [[Theodore Morse]] | Language = English | Form = }} '''We'll Knock The Heligo—Into Heligo—Out Of Heligoland!''' is a [[World War I]] song written by John J. O'Brian and composed by [[Theodore Morse]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Vogel |first1=Frederick G. |date=1995 |title=World War I Songs: A History and Dictionary of Popular American Patriotic Tunes, with Over 300 Complete Lyrics |location=Jefferson |publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc. |page=262 |isbn=0-89950-952-5}} {{OCLC | 32241433}}</ref> The song was first published in 1917 by [[Leo Feist Inc.]], in [[New York, NY]]. The sheet music cover depicts a terrified Kaiser standing on a cliff with a city below and United States soldiers rushing toward him.<ref>{{cite book |last=Parker |first=Bernard S. |year=2007 |title=World War I Sheet Music Vol 2. |location=Jefferson |publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc. |page=762 |isbn=978-0-7864-2798-7 |oclc=71790113}}</ref>
The sheet music can be found at the [[Pritzker Military Museum & Library]].<ref>Morse, Theodore F., and John O'Brien. 1917. ''We'll knock the Heligo-- into Heligo-- out of Heligoland!'' New York: Leo Feist Inc. {{OCLC|71225608}}</ref>
